page.title: 05CREDITS
page.content:
The area has been surveyed and written about by members of the Combe Martin Historical Society with the assistance of friends and neighbours.
The photograph was supplied by the Exmoor Park Warden and the information was recorded on disk by a member of the Society.
It is regretted that the information is not more comprehensive but the deadline only allowed about ten days for the Society to collect information on this block and the one to the north of it. This allowed no time to take photographs and get them processed and the only one we could find is typical of the area but not actually of part of it.
